    <section>
        <h2>5. MATHEMATICAL FOUNDATION</h2>
        <p>The mass of Dark Matter ($M$) within a certain radius ($r$) can be calculated by observing the velocity ($v$) of stars:</p>
        <div class="formula">
            M(r) = (v² * r) / G
        </div>
        <p><i>This simple equation proved that there is far more mass in galaxies than what meets the eye.</i></p>
        
